1
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,750
[owl hooting]

2
00:00:45,125 --> 00:00:46,500
[MAN]
Pekanpe, huh?

3
00:00:46,583 --> 00:00:48,125
You've got a lot, there.

4
00:00:48,208 --> 00:00:50,750
I grabbed them as we passed
through Lake Touro.

5
00:00:50,833 --> 00:00:53,250
Uh, they look old.

6
00:00:53,333 --> 00:00:54,708
"Pekanpe" means

7
00:00:54,791 --> 00:00:56,666
"things which float
on the surface of the lake."

8
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:58,416
They're water chestnuts.

9
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,500
A staple for us during winter.

10
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:02,291
They're really thorny.

11
00:01:02,375 --> 00:01:04,541
I've heard that ancient ninjas
used to throw these things

12
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:07,333
on the ground to help impede
an enemy's advance.

13
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:09,333
Did they really?

14
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:11,000
[hooting]

15
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:18,458
Kotan-kor Kamuy
has been very noisy lately.

16
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:20,833
-[SUGIMOTO] Hmm?
-[ASIRPA] It's a type of owl.

17
00:01:20,916 --> 00:01:23,083
A kamuy that protects
the village.

18
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:24,833
It yells at the demons
that come down

19
00:01:24,916 --> 00:01:26,666
from the tops of the mountains.

20
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:29,708
[MAN] We can't just rely
on the kamuy for everything.

21
00:01:29,791 --> 00:01:31,750
If they come,
the village men will be ready

22
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:33,958
and willing to risk
their lives to fight.

23
00:01:34,041 --> 00:01:35,666
Who's "they"?

24
00:01:35,750 --> 00:01:37,291
There's a group of bandits
that have come

25
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:39,208
to live in this area.

26
00:01:39,291 --> 00:01:41,250
They attack at night,
moving through the forest

27
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:44,000
without even torches
to light the way.

28
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,958
Thing is, the light would make
no difference to them,

29
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:49,125
because they're all blind.

30
00:01:49,208 --> 00:01:52,000
One of our people got a look
at them during an attack.

31
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:54,166
Apparently, the man
who's leading them

32
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:56,041
has some strange tattoos.

33
00:01:56,125 --> 00:01:57,500
[ALL gasp]

34
00:01:59,125 --> 00:02:02,791
An escaped prisoner
from Abashiri, then.

35
00:02:02,875 --> 00:02:07,125
I bet it's a certain guy who was
doing hard labor on Mount Iwo.

36
00:02:07,208 --> 00:02:10,625
His name is Toni Anji.

37
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:44,166
[SHIRAISHI]
It was a commonly held belief

38
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:48,416
that nobody sent to Mount Iwo
ever came back.

39
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:50,333
"Iwo" means "sulfur."

40
00:03:50,416 --> 00:03:54,458
It's a critical resource used
in gunpowder and other things.

41
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:57,583
Unfortunately, mining it
releases sulfuric acid gas

42
00:03:57,666 --> 00:04:01,208
which damages the eyesight
of those forced to dig it up.

43
00:04:01,291 --> 00:04:03,750
It only took six months
for the entire operation

44
00:04:03,833 --> 00:04:05,458
to be shut down.

45
00:04:05,541 --> 00:04:07,333
And in that time, 42 died,

46
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:09,666
and who knows
how many went blind.

47
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,916
I heard a rumor that it was
secretly restarted, though.

48
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:15,291
And that Warden Inudou
is lending out prisoners

49
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:16,958
for the hard labor.

50
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:19,291
Anyway, I bet the ones
who escaped

51
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:22,125
before they were killed
are these bandits in the woods.

52
00:04:22,208 --> 00:04:23,500
During the last new moon,

53
00:04:23,583 --> 00:04:25,875
the village closest to ours
was attacked.

54
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:27,916
These men are very careful.

55
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,208
They attack villages together
in large groups

56
00:04:30,291 --> 00:04:31,708
and they always do it
on a new moon

57
00:04:31,791 --> 00:04:33,000
when there's no light.

58
00:04:33,083 --> 00:04:34,916
Who knows when they'll attack.

59
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,583
It'd be faster
to find their hideout

60
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:38,125
than wait through the moon.

61
00:04:38,208 --> 00:04:40,041
There's a Japanese family
that runs an inn

62
00:04:40,125 --> 00:04:41,916
and hot springs fairly close by.

63
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,708
Perhaps you could learn
something from them?

64
00:04:43,791 --> 00:04:45,000
Hot springs?

65
00:04:45,083 --> 00:04:46,291
That sounds amazing.

66
00:04:46,375 --> 00:04:48,083
I would kill for a bath.

67
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:50,666
[clicking]

68
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,416
Whatcha doin'?

69
00:04:56,500 --> 00:04:57,666
Is something wrong?

70
00:04:57,750 --> 00:04:59,000
No.

71
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:01,208
Just heard a sound
I've never heard before.

72
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:05,750
Hmm.

73
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:08,875
Maybe I imagined it.

74
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:12,041
[hooting]

75
00:05:13,666 --> 00:05:14,875
[OLD MAN]
I've had my hands

76
00:05:14,958 --> 00:05:17,541
on lots of different bodies
in my time,

77
00:05:17,625 --> 00:05:21,958
but I swear I've never seen
such soft muscle before.

78
00:05:22,041 --> 00:05:24,250
My hands sink into it.

79
00:05:24,333 --> 00:05:26,166
You're like a big cat.

80
00:05:26,250 --> 00:05:28,916
Well, maybe a tiger.

81
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,750
What a wonderful gift
heaven has given you.

82
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:33,458
But these,

83
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:36,666
the deep wounds that you have
scattered all over your body,

84
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,375
tell me, how were you
able to survive?

85
00:05:39,458 --> 00:05:41,458
[SUGIMOTO]
The Ainu have a custom.

86
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:43,250
During their funerals,
the deceased person's

87
00:05:43,333 --> 00:05:45,625
possessions are damaged
or destroyed.

88
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,041
That removes their souls,

89
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:50,166
so their owner can use them
in the next world.

90
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:53,958
If you want to remove my soul,

91
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:56,250
you'd need a bigger wound
than any of these.

92
00:05:57,791 --> 00:05:59,458
[ASIRPA]
Their souls only leave

93
00:05:59,541 --> 00:06:02,250
because they've finished
their job in this world.

94
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,916
I think the reason your wounds
have never killed you,

95
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,666
is that you still haven't
finished the job

96
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,000
you were meant to do.

97
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:14,208
[SUGIMOTO] I asked the masseuse
about the area.

98
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,625
He said there used to be
more hot spring inns

99
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:18,125
around here a while back.

100
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:20,041
Once they shut down Mount Iwo,

101
00:06:20,125 --> 00:06:22,041
most of them closed up shop,

102
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:24,041
but the old buildings
are still in the forest.

103
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,916
[SHIRAISHI] Perfect places
for bandits to hide then, huh?

104
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:30,208
Anybody else up
for some hunting at dawn?

105
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:31,875
[MALE VOICE]
Wow!

106
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:36,708
[ASIRPA]
Would you like any help?

107
00:06:36,791 --> 00:06:38,500
That's very kind.

108
00:06:38,583 --> 00:06:41,666
But I'm more fit to walk
at night than you.

109
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:42,875
[ASIRPA]
Really?

110
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:44,166
[OLD MAN]
Indeed.

111
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,666
The blind don't see
with our eyes,

112
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,750
but that doesn't mean
we don't see.

113
00:06:50,541 --> 00:06:52,750
A little tip, keep an ear out

114
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:55,708
for the sound of clogs
in the night.

115
00:06:55,791 --> 00:06:57,041
What do you mean?

116
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,333
There's a certain sound
the blind bandits

117
00:06:59,416 --> 00:07:01,333
make in the forest at night.

118
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:04,083
Everyone believes
it's the sound of clogs.

119
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:05,500
But they've got it wrong.

120
00:07:05,583 --> 00:07:07,125
[click echoing]

121
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:09,583
[OLD MAN] I'll never forget
the first time I heard it.

122
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,291
It's actually their tongues,
you see.

123
00:07:13,375 --> 00:07:17,458
They make a clicking noise
and use the echoes to see.

124
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:19,208
And the noise?

125
00:07:19,291 --> 00:07:21,541
What exactly does
the click sound like?

126
00:07:23,625 --> 00:07:24,541
[click echoing]

127
00:07:24,625 --> 00:07:26,000
What the hell is that?

128
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:30,041
[ASIRPA]
They've got us.

129
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:32,583
This whole time,
they've been tracking us.

130
00:07:32,666 --> 00:07:33,875
♪

131
00:07:35,708 --> 00:07:37,041
Who the hell are you?

132
00:07:37,125 --> 00:07:39,375
More over here.

133
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:40,333
[groans]

134
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:42,666
[groans]

135
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,083
[SHIRAISHI]
That guy's Toni Anji!

136
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:47,208
[clicks tongue]

137
00:07:50,375 --> 00:07:51,916
[SUGIMOTO]
It's too dark for us

138
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,041
to even see,
let alone fight.

139
00:07:54,125 --> 00:07:56,125
And our dicks are out?!

140
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:58,875
Sorry, did we catch you
at a bad time?

141
00:07:58,958 --> 00:08:00,708
Is that Shiraishi's voice?

142
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,500
Did you get hired on as a miner?

143
00:08:02,583 --> 00:08:05,083
[grunts]
We're not here to deal with you!

144
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,833
Just let us copy down
your tattoo

145
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:08,125
and we'll give you a share!

146
00:08:08,208 --> 00:08:10,125
The way I see it,
you'd have shot by now

147
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:12,291
if you weren't willing
to make a deal.

148
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:14,833
Nah, I'm just trying
to not hit the kid.

149
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:17,666
Now's your chance to get him out
before I start shooting.

150
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,416
-[gasps]
-[RYU barking]

151
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,333
[snarling]

152
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:22,458
Hey, that was Ryu!

153
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:29,125
It's too noisy to make
anything out for sure.

154
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:30,583
Go on, get him out of here.

155
00:08:30,666 --> 00:08:32,333
Come on, let's go hide
in the forest!

156
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:33,625
-[groans]
-[thuds]

157
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:37,166
♪

158
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:40,250
[BANDIT]
Got him.

159
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:43,166
[groaning]

160
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:45,625
[grunting]

161
00:08:45,708 --> 00:08:49,291
It'll take a lot more than this
if you wanna kill me!

162
00:08:49,375 --> 00:08:50,625
-[clicks tongue]
-[gasps]

163
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,333
A gunshot.

164
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,916
[TANIGAKI] Toni Anji seems to be
the only one with a gun.

165
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,166
Maybe so they won't
shoot each other?

166
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,375
[KIRORANKE] They even approached
us from the direction of the inn

167
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:06,166
in order to keep us from
running toward the light.

168
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,041
They're obviously masters
at using the dark

169
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,375
to their advantage.

170
00:09:09,458 --> 00:09:11,333
Ogata was the only one
who was smart enough

171
00:09:11,416 --> 00:09:14,083
to stash his gun
near the hot springs.

172
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:16,166
We'll never hear
the end of that.

173
00:09:19,666 --> 00:09:21,416
Hmm? [sniffing]

174
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:24,166
♪

175
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:26,125
Huh? Sugimoto.

176
00:09:26,208 --> 00:09:27,250
[BANDIT]
Put out the light.

177
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,166
♪

178
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:32,125
You're gonna get yourself shot!

179
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:33,583
One of these guys has a gun!

180
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:34,625
[gunshot]

181
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:36,791
[gasps]

182
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:41,916
[shouting]

183
00:09:45,375 --> 00:09:46,916
[clicks tongue]

184
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,041
[OGATA]
Can't see a thing.

185
00:09:50,125 --> 00:09:52,250
And only four shots left.

186
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,500
Better not waste 'em.

187
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:03,625
[gasps, yells]

188
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:05,000
[SUGIMOTO whispering]
Asirpa, it's me.

189
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:06,083
Hmm?

190
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:10,875
[ASIRPA]
All this blood, is it yours?

191
00:10:11,916 --> 00:10:13,208
Are you badly hurt?

192
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:14,833
I'm fine.

193
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:17,958
If it wasn't so damn dark,
they would be no match for me.

194
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:23,833
If we survive till dawn,
we'll counterattack.

195
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:27,083
[TONI]
Hmm. I think I smell blood.

196
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,541
♪

197
00:10:32,666 --> 00:10:34,375
[sniffing]

198
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:39,583
[clicking tongue]

199
00:10:56,166 --> 00:10:58,208
[WILK]
Are you really leaving?

200
00:10:58,291 --> 00:10:59,541
I'll miss you.

201
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,791
I know.
Goodbye, Wilk.

202
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,125
[WILK]
Inkarmat.

203
00:11:05,208 --> 00:11:07,000
This was my mother's.

204
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:10,083
I know that girls grow up
and change in no time.

205
00:11:10,166 --> 00:11:13,750
Soon, you'll be even
more beautiful.

206
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,333
But if you'll wear this,

207
00:11:15,416 --> 00:11:17,666
I'll recognize you
when we meet again.

208
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:20,083
Isn't it important to you?

209
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:22,666
[WILK]
Yes, but so are you.

210
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,750
[INKARMAT]
Thank you.

211
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:27,666
But I already know
that I'm never going to

212
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,000
see your face again.

213
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:32,708
That's what my fortune-telling
said my fate would be.

214
00:11:34,833 --> 00:11:36,041
[TANIGAKI]
Inkarmat.

215
00:11:36,125 --> 00:11:39,000
Hmm?
Tanigaki Nispa.

216
00:11:43,208 --> 00:11:44,583
Where is Cikapasi?

217
00:11:44,666 --> 00:11:46,958
I told him to hide and stay put.

218
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:49,416
If he's careful, the bandits
shouldn't find him.

219
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:50,666
[INKARMAT]
Let's hope so.

220
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:53,583
[clicking tongue]

221
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,875
-[ALL gasp]
-[clicking continues]

222
00:11:57,958 --> 00:12:01,500
Here they come.
I have an idea. Follow me.

223
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:03,375
Hey, let's go. Come on.

224
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:05,416
♪

225
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:08,625
[KIRORANKE]
I found this place today.

226
00:12:08,708 --> 00:12:10,708
If we cross the lake and take
the long route back,

227
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:11,958
we should be able to make it

228
00:12:12,041 --> 00:12:13,666
to the inn
without them finding us.

229
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:18,250
Climb on board.

230
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,625
What is it, something wrong?

231
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:21,041
I'm sorry.

232
00:12:21,125 --> 00:12:22,791
I'm afraid I can't swim.

233
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:27,250
And I have
a terrible premonition.

234
00:12:28,500 --> 00:12:31,000
Don't worry, I've handled boats
like this since I was a kid,

235
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,541
and I've gone fishing at night.

236
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:33,458
I know what I'm doing.

237
00:12:33,541 --> 00:12:36,458
[clicking tongue]

238
00:12:36,541 --> 00:12:38,375
Think about it,
if I really wanted you gone,

239
00:12:38,458 --> 00:12:40,416
then wouldn't I just
leave you here to die?

240
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,916
Get your ass in the boat!

241
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,375
[shudders]

242
00:12:54,125 --> 00:12:56,000
[TONI]
Little more to the left.

243
00:12:56,083 --> 00:12:57,250
Throw another one.

244
00:13:00,791 --> 00:13:02,000
[ALL gasp]

245
00:13:02,083 --> 00:13:03,833
-They're judging distance!
-[screams]

246
00:13:07,750 --> 00:13:08,958
Tanigaki Nispa!

247
00:13:29,041 --> 00:13:30,708
♪

248
00:13:42,208 --> 00:13:43,333
[INKARMAT]
Oh, I see.

249
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:45,875
It's my time.

250
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:49,166
You're sending me
to the next world, aren't you?

251
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:52,833
This is my fate.

252
00:13:54,833 --> 00:13:56,875
To die without ever
seeing him again.

253
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:01,250
The fortunes spoke true.

254
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:05,541
♪

255
00:14:37,625 --> 00:14:39,041
[panting]

256
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:41,791
[BOTH gasp]

257
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:45,208
[ALL panting]

258
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:51,125
Are you all right?

259
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:53,083
How badly were you hit?

260
00:14:53,166 --> 00:14:54,166
[TANIGAKI]
I'll be fine.

261
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:55,625
The bullet went clean through.

262
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:58,000
[laughs]

263
00:14:58,083 --> 00:15:00,083
[TANIGAKI]
Seriously? You're laughing?

264
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:01,416
Kind of.

265
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,291
I just had the strangest dream.

266
00:15:04,375 --> 00:15:06,291
I was remembering it.

267
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:07,500
Hmm.

268
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:10,875
[moans]

269
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,250
[INKARMAT]
Now I know.

270
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,000
We can change our fate.

271
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:21,291
Sorry to interrupt your fun
but we should really go.

272
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,208
-[groans]
-Huh?

273
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,750
He can see us!

274
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:31,625
♪

275
00:15:33,708 --> 00:15:35,000
Dawn is coming.

276
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:36,666
Hurry, keep moving!

277
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:38,500
We'll be totally exposed here.

278
00:15:38,583 --> 00:15:40,041
[mumbles]

279
00:15:40,125 --> 00:15:42,416
[RYU barking]

280
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:43,708
Ryu?

281
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,416
[grunting]

282
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,708
Now the tables have turned.

283
00:15:54,791 --> 00:15:55,958
Sugimoto!

284
00:15:56,041 --> 00:15:58,875
♪

285
00:16:01,083 --> 00:16:02,375
[SUGIMOTO]
Ogata.

286
00:16:02,458 --> 00:16:05,208
Toni Anji and his men
just went inside.

287
00:16:05,291 --> 00:16:07,458
This is their hideout.

288
00:16:07,541 --> 00:16:10,500
[SUGIMOTO] If we go back
to get our guns, they'll escape.

289
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:12,750
Let's head inside
and finish this right now.

290
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,958
I want you to stay outside,
you got it?

291
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:18,958
♪

292
00:16:22,708 --> 00:16:23,833
[SUGIMOTO]
It's dark.

293
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:25,250
I'm gonna open the windows.

294
00:16:28,791 --> 00:16:30,000
[grunts]

295
00:16:30,083 --> 00:16:31,375
Are you kidding me?

296
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:33,458
They nailed
all the windows shut.

297
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:36,750
[ASIRPA]
Sugimoto!

298
00:16:36,833 --> 00:16:38,875
♪

299
00:16:42,541 --> 00:16:43,791
-[clicks tongue]
-Go, now!

300
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:46,250
[panting]

301
00:16:56,458 --> 00:16:57,666
[ASIRPA]
Sugimoto?

302
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,458
Huh? Asirpa?

303
00:16:59,541 --> 00:17:01,041
How'd you get in here?

304
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:02,416
Where's Ogata?

305
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,916
[SUGIMOTO whispering]
We split up.

306
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,750
[ASIRPA]
It's not safe to move.

307
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:08,166
-What do we do?
-[clicking tongue]

308
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:09,708
Where is it coming from?

309
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:13,208
I can't see anything.

310
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,666
But this is their home.

311
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:19,375
They can see us perfectly.

312
00:17:19,458 --> 00:17:21,958
[clicking continues]

313
00:17:24,041 --> 00:17:25,875
[groans sharply]

314
00:17:25,958 --> 00:17:26,916
That's pekanpe.

315
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,750
[groaning]

316
00:17:28,833 --> 00:17:30,125
[grunting]

317
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:35,208
[clicks tongue]

318
00:17:37,125 --> 00:17:38,791
[groaning]

319
00:17:38,875 --> 00:17:40,666
[grunting]

320
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:42,250
[grunting]

321
00:17:44,791 --> 00:17:47,041
You deserve every single bit
of this and more!

322
00:17:47,125 --> 00:17:48,500
You miners and Warden Inudou

323
00:17:48,583 --> 00:17:50,541
must be made to suffer
the way we did!

324
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,291
We're gonna take back everything
you've gained

325
00:17:52,375 --> 00:17:54,458
by stealing the prisoners'
lives and sight.

326
00:17:54,541 --> 00:17:56,000
[grunting]

327
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:02,375
[SUGIMOTO] Take this,
you goddamned bastard!

328
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:04,958
Where are you, Sugimoto?
Are you okay?

329
00:18:05,041 --> 00:18:07,125
Asirpa, stay where you are!
Don't move!

330
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:08,333
Look at me.

331
00:18:08,416 --> 00:18:10,833
You attacked
innocent Ainu villages.

332
00:18:10,916 --> 00:18:14,458
Justice isn't on your side.
You're thieves!

333
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:16,208
Yes, you're right.

334
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:18,416
But it's the only way
for us to survive.

335
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:20,500
Now that we're
starving and blind.

336
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:23,250
We never killed anybody
who was innocent.

337
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:28,541
Whether that's true or not,
you're eventually going to.

338
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:30,416
[TONI]
You can tell, huh?

339
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,666
Even I can see it, you know.

340
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:36,000
No matter what, you can never go
back to who you were before,

341
00:18:36,083 --> 00:18:37,666
isn't that right?

342
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,583
♪

343
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,583
[BOTH grunting]

344
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:52,833
[HIJIKATA] It's been
a long time, Toni Anji.

345
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,625
That voice.

346
00:18:55,708 --> 00:18:58,125
What the hell are you
doing here, you old man?

347
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:02,250
Oh, not much,
just fighting Warden Inudou.

348
00:19:06,916 --> 00:19:08,625
Hmm. Well, well.

349
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:10,750
We meet again, miss.

350
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,166
[ASIRPA]
Dick-sensei.

351
00:19:13,541 --> 00:19:15,708
How were you able to find us?

352
00:19:15,791 --> 00:19:18,708
[HIJIKATA]
The dog outside helped us.

353
00:19:18,791 --> 00:19:20,875
We had information
that Toni Anji

354
00:19:20,958 --> 00:19:23,583
was lurking around in this area.

355
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:26,166
Sugimoto, would you be willing

356
00:19:26,250 --> 00:19:28,958
to leave Toni for us
to deal with in our own way?

357
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:32,083
As long as you let me
copy his tattoos, I don't care.

358
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:36,125
Although, Asirpa's relatives
do live right around here.

359
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,291
Probably better
to be safe than sorry.

360
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:41,083
Just go ahead and kill him
and skin him.

361
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:43,791
[ASIRPA] You live
in the darkness, always hiding.

362
00:19:43,875 --> 00:19:47,750
Coming out only at night,
simply to harm others.

363
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,625
If you continue to do this,

364
00:19:49,708 --> 00:19:52,750
your life will never
be anything but darkness.

365
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:53,833
[gasps]

366
00:19:55,458 --> 00:19:58,000
Damn it, I know you're right.

367
00:19:58,083 --> 00:20:00,166
♪

368
00:20:01,333 --> 00:20:02,875
That's what
the warden's doing.

369
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:05,333
Lending out prisoners to work
Mount Iwo,

370
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:08,083
and then using
all that money to buy weapons.

371
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:10,125
I saw he even
had a Maxim gun.

372
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:12,083
If I had to guess,
I'd say it's likely

373
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:14,333
that he's hiding
other powerful weapons again.

374
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:19,208
[TSURUMI] But they caught you
before you were able to discover

375
00:20:19,291 --> 00:20:22,541
where those weapons
were being held, so...

376
00:20:22,625 --> 00:20:24,791
that's quite
a disappointing turn,

377
00:20:24,875 --> 00:20:26,791
wouldn't you agree,
Private Usami?

378
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:27,958
[gasps]

379
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,208
[TSURUMI]
Tsukishima, sit him down.

380
00:20:32,375 --> 00:20:34,958
Do you have any inkling
or even spark of an idea

381
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:36,750
how difficult it was
to get you hired on

382
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:38,333
as a guard there, to begin with?

383
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:39,791
Do you care to wager a guess?

384
00:20:39,875 --> 00:20:41,541
[USAMI]
He's touching me!

385
00:20:41,625 --> 00:20:43,625
[TSURUMI] I'm going to draw
a little stick figure

386
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,125
on this mole and make it run.

387
00:20:45,208 --> 00:20:47,375
How about that?
Won't that be cute?

388
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:50,791
Ha! It's running
on his dumb face!

389
00:20:50,875 --> 00:20:53,125
[TSURUMI] I'll make
the other mole run, too.

390
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:54,583
Why not, right?

391
00:20:54,666 --> 00:20:56,166
[USAMI]
My head is going to explode.

392
00:20:56,250 --> 00:20:57,916
[laughing]

393
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,375
[heavy breathing]

394
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:01,250
[TSURUMI] Aw, look,
those two moles are running

395
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:02,958
just as fast as they can.

396
00:21:03,041 --> 00:21:05,583
But tragically there's no way
they'll ever get any closer,

397
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:07,708
no matter how hard they try.

398
00:21:07,791 --> 00:21:09,500
Those poor things!

399
00:21:13,291 --> 00:21:16,625
So, both Inkarmat and Kiroranke.

400
00:21:16,708 --> 00:21:18,375
I wish that I could just
write it all off

401
00:21:18,458 --> 00:21:20,541
as a trap of
Lieutenant Tsurumi's.

402
00:21:20,625 --> 00:21:23,291
I've called an old friend
of mine to the city.

403
00:21:23,375 --> 00:21:24,791
I've had suspicions of my own

404
00:21:24,875 --> 00:21:27,958
and I'm ready
to find some answers.

405
00:21:28,041 --> 00:21:29,375
I'll take photos of both of them

406
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:32,333
and have someone
look into it for us.

407
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:34,791
Why are we taking photos
all of a sudden?

408
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:37,333
[SUGIMOTO] I wanted to send
a picture of Asirpa

409
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:38,958
back to Huci.

410
00:21:39,041 --> 00:21:40,750
But since we're here,

411
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,708
I figured we should
all take one.

412
00:21:46,208 --> 00:21:49,083
Hijikata, I think I should
finally give you

413
00:21:49,166 --> 00:21:52,416
what I've been keeping
safe here for so long.

414
00:21:52,500 --> 00:21:53,833
♪

415
00:21:53,916 --> 00:21:56,250
[HIJIKATA]
Ha. Hmm.

416
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:01,375
[TONI]
Sugimoto is his name, you said?

417
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:02,708
The strange thing is,

418
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:05,625
I felt something familiar
when fighting him.

419
00:22:05,708 --> 00:22:07,291
I was struck by it.

420
00:22:07,375 --> 00:22:09,833
He reminded me
of a young Hijikata,

421
00:22:09,916 --> 00:22:12,125
back when I first
met him in Abashiri.

422
00:22:13,833 --> 00:22:16,041
Fierce as a demon.

423
00:22:16,125 --> 00:22:18,291
But somehow kind, as well.

424
00:23:51,166 --> 00:23:53,958
[TANIGAKI]
Um, do I really have to strip?

425
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,125
[OLD MAN]
Everybody else did.

426
00:23:57,208 --> 00:23:58,625
Looking good.

427
00:23:58,708 --> 00:24:01,166
Spread your legs a little bit
more for me, though.

428
00:24:01,250 --> 00:24:02,166
[camera shutter clicks]

429
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:04,791
♪

430
00:24:06,708 --> 00:24:10,291
[NARRATOR] Next time,
"On the Night of the New Moon."

